==English==

===Etymology===
From {{af|en|waxing|moon|nocat=1}}. Compare {{cog|enm|wexinge of the mone}}, {{m|enm|þe waxyng of moone}}, {{m|enm|waxinge of þe mone}}, {{m|enm|wexinge of þe mone|lit=(the) waxing of the moon}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[wax]]ing [[moon]]}}

# The [[moon]] when it appears larger each night as it progresses from a [[new moon]] to a [[full moon]].

